{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Test the riskiest assumption behind Codex CLI config file discovery behavior first.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fbb4210d20319f2ac","fcd9d2efb49372cae"],"move_id":"4","move_name":"riskiest-assumption test","subject":"Codex CLI config file discovery behavior"},{"coaching":"Plan how actual tracked CLAUDE.md reference count will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f876f85c195ec8f05"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"actual tracked CLAUDE.md reference count"},{"coaching":"Pin down unclassified docs/experiments CLAUDE.md references with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f1676df35935d7765","fd6771c3c9b6de547"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"unclassified docs/experiments CLAUDE.md references"},{"coaching":"Consider a short spike to de-risk generated-file regeneration workflow for criteria guide before committing the plan.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f40e71d65191d7c75"],"move_id":"1","move_name":"spike","subject":"generated-file regeneration workflow for criteria guide"},{"coaching":"Pin down replacement target string in LLM routing files with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f13b2a61f8a8cea11","f6824b30e8cad96d1"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"replacement target string in LLM routing files"},{"coaching":"Plan how AC removal-and-replacement verification gap will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f4f53e14b24f52860","fefe1425f25423224"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC removal-and-replacement verification gap"},{"coaching":"Plan how AC1 and AC2 overlap and redundancy will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f2c084c3cbd82437b","f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC1 and AC2 overlap and redundancy"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for conflict between two tracked codex config files.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f5898546ab2d21979","fda73f1b748c9a0ca"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"conflict between two tracked codex config files"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for Antigravity as new unvetted provider config surface — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f26709a26748e177e"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"Antigravity as new unvetted provider config surface"},{"coaching":"Pin down AC1 provability within a single story's working session with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f6f036c8c1ede2c7e"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"AC1 provability within a single story's working session"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":17,"blocking":0,"dropped":6,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":4,"ran":true,"references":4,"resolved":1,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":3},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":4722,"file_impact":4,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":64,"verify_lint_abstained":59},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1204,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":4,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["A1","E1"],"floored_finding_ids":["f2c084c3cbd82437b","f26709a26748e177e"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":205.9,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":454273.6,"total_ms":454609.4,"verify_requests":15},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify (against `codex --help` output or the official Codex config-reference docs) that Codex CLI reads a repo-root `.codex/config.toml` in addition to `~/.codex/config.toml`; if it does not, revise the approach (e.g., update CONTRIBUTING.md to instruct developers to copy the file, or document the limitation).","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/session-id-shims.md:91: 'Copy [scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml] into `~/.codex/config.toml`'","scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml:2: '# Copy this fragment into ~/.codex/config.toml'","Plan states: 'bring .codex/config.toml under version control ... pointing at AGENTS.md'","No evidence in repo that Codex reads a repo-root .codex/ directory; Evidence class: Unverified"],"finding":"The plan commits `.codex/config.toml` at the repo root and asserts Codex CLI will read it to pick up the `AGENTS.md` pointer, but the existing repo documentation (docs/session-id-shims.md:91, scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml:2) consistently directs users to copy the fragment into `~/.codex/config.toml` (user home directory). Whether Codex CLI discovers and reads a repo-root `.codex/config.toml` rather than only the home-dir location is an unverified capability assertion. If Codex only reads from `~HOME`, the committed file is silently a no-op and the epic goal ('guidance available to Codex') remains unmet.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbb4210d20319f2ac","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the Codex config' bullet; AC line 3 (.codex/config.toml tracking)","norm_id":"n24a3ae5316b907ea","priority":0.7778,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A developer clones the repo; Codex CLI ignores the repo-root .codex/config.toml because it only reads ~/.codex/config.toml; the agent sees no AGENTS.md pointer; the epic goal is silently unmet while AC#3 passes (git-tracked + grep).","CI gate turns green but no Codex instance actually loads the committed config."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Check the Codex config-reference page (https://developers.openai.com/codex/config-reference) for config-discovery order. If only the home-dir location is supported, replace the 'commit to repo root' approach with 'commit a copyable template at scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml (already tracked) and update CONTRIBUTING.md with copy instructions'.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile the '24 refs' count against the actual git grep output and explicitly account for each CLAUDE.md hit in docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/ (criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500, make_crit_v7.py:181 and siblings) — either add them to the owned-files list, assign them to another story, or document why they are deliberately left unchanged.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'A git grep CLAUDE.md over tracked files gives the complete surface (24 refs).'","Search confirmed CLAUDE.md hits in docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v2.json:25, criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500, make_crit_v7.py:181 — all tracked files not listed in the owned set, not attributed to another story.","AC proof command excludes ':!docs/experiments' but the plan body contains no explanation for why those references are intentionally left unchanged.","Total visible hit count from search far exceeds 24 even before counting experiment-run JSONL files."],"finding":"The plan claims 'a git grep CLAUDE.md over tracked files gives the complete surface (24 refs)' but the actual tracked-file hit count substantially exceeds 24. The docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/ directory alone contains additional CLAUDE.md references (criteria_v2.json, criteria_v4.json, criteria_v5.json, criteria_v6.json, criteria_v8.json, criteria_v7.json, make_crit_v7.py) that are neither listed in the owned-files set, nor assigned to other stories, nor explained in the scope-exclusion narrative. The AC proof command silently excludes ':!docs/experiments' without any plan-body rationale — a false-exclusion risk.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f876f85c195ec8f05","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('a git grep CLAUDE.md over tracked files gives the complete surface (24 refs)') and AC proof command (first AC item)","norm_id":"n08cf0eef1bf315a1","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer running git grep before starting work will see ~10 additional CLAUDE.md refs in docs/experiments/ not accounted for in the plan, causing confusion about whether those files need updating.","The AC shell command passes even if docs/experiments/ files still reference CLAUDE.md, masking residual references in tracked criterion files (criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500 are actual criterion definitions, not just run logs)."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Deliberately NOT changed' bullet for docs/experiments/ explaining these are frozen historical experiment artifacts (like CHANGELOG.md), OR add criteria_v7.json, criteria_v8.json, make_crit_v7.py, and the remaining criteria_v*.json files to the owned list. Also update the reference count from '24' to the actual number.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Classify the CLAUDE.md occurrences in `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/` (criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500, make_crit_v7.py:181) as either: (a) owned by this story and added to the edit list, (b) historical/frozen artifacts to be excluded with explicit justification, or (c) assigned to a follow-up ticket — and update the AC1 exclusion comment accordingly.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v7.json:465: '\"check\": \"A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update.\"'","docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v8.json:500: same string","docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/make_crit_v7.py:181: same string in Python dict","Plan says 24 refs total, delegates/owns all but CHANGELOG(3), event-schema(S1), examples(S5) — the experiments hits are unaccounted for"],"finding":"The plan's AC1 proving command silently excludes ':!docs/experiments', but docs/experiments/ contains three unclassified CLAUDE.md references (criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500, make_crit_v7.py:181) that are neither in the owned-17 list, nor assigned to S1/S5, nor justified as historical records. After this story lands, those files will still carry CLAUDE.md and are not covered by any AC.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1676df35935d7765","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / AC1 proving command (':!docs/experiments' exclusion)","norm_id":"ndedfb34a6fd58981","priority":0.6375,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The 'experiments' criteria JSON files are the historical versioned snapshots of the criteria — they contain real CLAUDE.md strings that could mislead future LLM reviewers even after this story closes.","If the epic's goal is a clean AGENTS.md sweep, these files undermine it silently because they are excluded from verification."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a 4th 'Deliberately NOT changed' bullet: '`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/` — frozen historical snapshots of versioned criteria JSON files; rewriting them would falsify experiment provenance.' Then document the ':!docs/experiments' exclusion in the AC1 comment.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace the direct-edit instruction for `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md:462,467` with an explicit step: update `criteria_routing.json:407` and `plan_review_T5e.md:10`, then run `python -m rebar.llm.plan_review.registry regenerate-criteria-guide` to propagate the change to the generated guide.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md line 3: 'GENERATED from the criteria registry (`python -m rebar.llm.plan_review.registry regenerate-criteria-guide`) — do not hand-edit.'","Plan names direct edits to this file alongside criteria_routing.json and plan_review_T5e.md, as if they are three independent targets."],"finding":"The plan lists `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md` (lines 462, 467) as a direct edit target, but that file's header declares it is GENERATED by `python -m rebar.llm.plan_review.registry regenerate-criteria-guide` and must not be hand-edited. Direct edits will be overwritten the next time the registry regeneration command is run. The correct edit path is via criteria_routing.json + plan_review_T5e.md, then regenerating.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f40e71d65191d7c75","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md:462,467'","norm_id":"n247c28cac4ed93ea","priority":0.6375,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A contributor edits docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md directly, then someone else runs `make lint` or a regen script, and the manual edit is overwritten — the AC2 proving command then fails.","Alternatively the regen step is omitted, and docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md stays stale relative to the updated criteria_routing.json."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In the What section, change 'docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md:462,467' to a note: '(auto-regenerated from criteria_routing.json — run `python -m rebar.llm.plan_review.registry regenerate-criteria-guide` after updating criteria_routing.json and plan_review_T5e.md)'.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify and document in the plan that Codex CLI reads `.codex/config.toml` from the repository root (not only from `~/.codex/config.toml`); if it does not, either switch to the `scripts/session-shims/` + update-docs approach or reframe the AC as 'provides a copy-to-home template' rather than 'makes guidance available to Codex at runtime.'","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/session-id-shims.md line 91: 'Copy [scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml] into ~/.codex/config.toml'","scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml line 2: '# Copy this fragment into ~/.codex/config.toml'","Plan Why section: 'the epic's goal (guidance available to Codex/Cursor/Antigravity) is only met if the provider configs are committed'","No plan statement that Codex reads from repo-root `.codex/config.toml`"],"finding":"The plan commits `.codex/config.toml` to the repo root to make guidance 'available to Codex,' but the existing `docs/session-id-shims.md` (line 91) and `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` (line 2) both state that Codex reads its config from `~/.codex/config.toml` (user-home), not from a repo-root path. The plan does not verify or assert that Codex CLI actually reads from a repo-root `.codex/config.toml`. If it does not, committing the file achieves only source-control visibility — the same outcome already provided by the existing `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` — rather than the stated goal of making guidance 'available to' Codex at runtime.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcd9d2efb49372cae","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the Codex config' bullet; AC3: `.codex/config.toml` is git-tracked and points at `AGENTS.md`","norm_id":"n64b79ed247a27e52","priority":0.5667,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If Codex CLI only reads `~/.codex/config.toml`, committing `.codex/config.toml` to the repo root adds a file that is never loaded by Codex — the mechanism does not achieve the stated goal.","A developer clones the repo, Codex reads `~/.codex/config.toml` (empty or stale), sees no `AGENTS.md` pointer, and is guided by whatever their prior home config says."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify and cite the Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` `@`-import limitation with a link to official Antigravity docs or release notes, and record the version at which this constraint applies, so the chosen approach (summary-reference rather than direct include) is grounded.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","Search for 'Antigravity' across all tracked files returns zero repo hits — the provider is undocumented in the codebase","No external doc link, version pin, or prior-art citation accompanies the assertion"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports' as a known fact, but 'Antigravity' appears nowhere in the repo's documentation or codebase, and no citation, doc link, or version reference is provided. This is a load-bearing unverified capability assertion: the entire approach of writing a short-reference-and-summary file (rather than a symlink or `@`-import) depends on it being true.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe37363abdbdcfe89","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","norm_id":"n5f1720a84e7d38c7","priority":0.5667,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If Antigravity does support `@`-imports (or a `file:` include directive), the chosen approach (maintaining a manually-synced summary) creates permanent drift risk vs. the canonical AGENTS.md that could have been sourced directly.","A future maintainer has no way to verify the limitation or know when/if it changes."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a parenthetical citation in the What section, e.g.: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports (per [Antigravity docs vX.Y](URL)); a short reference-and-summary file is used rather than a symlink.' If the docs confirm a future inclusion mechanism, note the upgrade path.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the exact replacement text for the T5e `documentation` check string in `criteria_routing.json:407`, `plan_review_T5e.md:10`, and `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md:467` (e.g., `\"A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / AGENTS.md / design-doc update.\"`), and add an AC2-level grep that verifies the replacement text is present, not just that CLAUDE.md is absent.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan says: 'CLAUDE.md → AGENTS.md or the new docs home' — 'or the new docs home' is never resolved to a concrete path or wording.","AC2 proving command: `git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- src/rebar/llm docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md` — verifies only absence of CLAUDE.md, not presence of a correct replacement string.","Confirmed file content: criteria_routing.json:407 `\"check\": \"A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update.\"` — this is a machine-read instruction string consumed by the plan-review LLM; its post-change wording is unspecified.","plan_review_T5e.md:10 contains the matching prose string referencing CLAUDE.md — also a live LLM prompt with no specified replacement."],"finding":"The plan updates machine-read LLM routing/prompt strings in criteria_routing.json:407 and plan_review_T5e.md:10 from 'CLAUDE.md' to an unspecified replacement, but never defines what the replacement text should be — 'AGENTS.md or the new docs home' leaves the actual value undefined for the executor.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f13b2a61f8a8cea11","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section (bullet: 'This story updates'); AC#2; src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json:407; src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md:10","norm_id":"n087d84c9fa5881e0","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Executor writes 'AGENTS.md' into the check string but the canonical new home turns out to be docs/architecture.md or a different path — the LLM reviewer now issues incorrect documentation guidance to downstream plan authors.","Executor removes CLAUDE.md references but uses a freeform paraphrase that doesn't match the docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md mirror, causing the guide and the routing JSON to diverge in meaning."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add a line to the What section: 'In the T5e documentation check string, replace `CLAUDE.md` with `AGENTS.md`' and update AC2's proving command to also assert: `git grep -q 'AGENTS.md' -- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md`.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan updates `criteria_routing.json:407` and `plan_review_T5e.md:10` (both active LLM routing/prompt files) to replace `CLAUDE.md` with `AGENTS.md`, but never specifies what the replacement decision-rule text should be. The current rule reads 'A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update.' Since `AGENTS.md` is agent-operational guidance rather than an architectural decision record, a naive find-replace would leave the T5e reviewer prompt and routing schema instructing plan reviewers (LLM and human) to look for architectural decisions in `AGENTS.md` — a semantically incorrect processing rule. The plan needs to define the canonical replacement text for these decision rules.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6824b30e8cad96d1","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json:407` and `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md:10`; plan AC bullet 2","norm_id":"n0271c102cbe76e42","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In the What section, add a note clarifying the canonical replacement: if `AGENTS.md` subsumes the developer-guide role (and thus is a valid place to record significant decisions), state that explicitly; otherwise change the replacement text in all three files to `'ADR / design-doc update'` (dropping the `CLAUDE.md` slot entirely) so the live LLM prompt remains semantically accurate.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a complementary check to AC1's proving command (or a new AC) that verifies AGENTS.md is present in the updated owned files — e.g. `git grep -l 'AGENTS\\.md' -- <owned-file-list>` — so the criterion covers both removal and replacement.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"[ \\\"$(git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\\\.md' -- ':!CLAUDE.md' ':!CHANGELOG.md' ':!docs/event-schema.md' ':!examples' ':!docs/experiments' | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\\\" = 0 ]\" — checks only for absence","Plan body: 'CLAUDE.md → AGENTS.md or the new docs home' — replacement is the stated intent","For migrations, criteria verify BOTH removal and replacement (E1 rule)"],"finding":"AC1's proving command only verifies REMOVAL of CLAUDE.md references but not REPLACEMENT with AGENTS.md. A contributor could delete all CLAUDE.md occurrences (or replace them with an unrelated string) and AC1 would pass while the actual migration goal — pointing consumers at AGENTS.md — goes unverified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4f53e14b24f52860","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command","norm_id":"ncc486e97f6388543","priority":0.4125,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer deletes CLAUDE.md lines outright without inserting AGENTS.md; CI passes; consumers of the docs find no pointer to AGENTS.md.","Implementer substitutes a different target (e.g. README.md) and AC1 still passes."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Append to AC1: `&& [ \"$(git grep -lc 'AGENTS\\.md' -- CONTRIBUTING.md README.md rebar.toml docs/architecture.md docs/api-stability.md docs/exit-codes.md docs/jira-sync-setup.md docs/llm-framework.md docs/releasing.md docs/workflow-editor.md docs/workflow-engine.md 'docs/adr/0043*' docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md scripts/jira-pressure-test/e2e_field_validation_probe.sh src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py | wc -l)\" = \"17\" ]`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The migration ACs verify removal of CLAUDE.md references for the ~15 non-src owned files but do not verify replacement with AGENTS.md, violating the E1 migration rule that criteria verify BOTH removal and replacement.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fefe1425f25423224","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC#1 (global zero-reference check); What section (list of ~15 docs/scripts files)","norm_id":"n9001517a193dee6b","priority":0.4125,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["vague/subjective terms present: clean","verify command `[ \"$(git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- ':!CLAUDE.md' ':!CHANGELOG.md' ':!docs/event-schema.md' ':!examples' ':!docs/experiments' | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\" = 0 ]` has an unquoted shell variable ($VAR/$?) in its grep — it expands before grep runs; the pattern is not what you wrote","verify command `[ \"$(git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- src/rebar/llm docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\" = 0 ]` has an unquoted shell variable ($VAR/$?) in its grep — it expands before grep runs; the pattern is not what you wrote"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify the relationship between the proposed `.codex/config.toml` and the existing `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` — either extend/supersede the existing file, deprecate one, or add a comment in each explaining the division of responsibility (AGENTS.md pointer vs. session-shim env injection).","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml already exists and is tracked with the same purpose: configuring the Codex shell_environment_policy","tests/unit/test_harness_shims.py:22: `_CODEX_TOML = _SHIMS / \"codex-config.toml\"` — the existing file is under active test coverage","docs/session-id-shims.md:90: 'Copy [scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml] into ~/.codex/config.toml' — users are already instructed to copy the existing shim","Plan says commit `.codex/config.toml` 'pointing at AGENTS.md, comment updated to the completed state' — but the existing shim content is about shell_environment_policy, not AGENTS.md, making the two files serve different concerns without the plan disambiguating"],"finding":"The plan commits a new `.codex/config.toml` at the repo root, but `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` is already tracked, tested (test_harness_shims.py:22 — `_CODEX_TOML = _SHIMS / \"codex-config.toml\"`), and documented in `docs/session-id-shims.md:90`. Adding a second tracked Codex config file without explaining which supersedes which, or how the two relate, is a config-surface proliferation.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5898546ab2d21979","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the Codex config' bullet; AC line 3","norm_id":"n75ff255ba4d42ee8","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A developer follows docs/session-id-shims.md and copies scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml to ~/.codex/config.toml, then discovers a tracked .codex/config.toml in the repo that appears to be the same file but with different content — they cannot tell which to use.","The CI test test_codex_config_is_valid_toml_and_sets_harness tests only the scripts/session-shims path; the new .codex/config.toml is untested and diverges silently."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Rather than creating a second Codex config file, extend `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` with the AGENTS.md pointer (as a comment in the `additionalContext` or equivalent field), keeping a single tracked source. Update `docs/session-id-shims.md` and the AC proving command accordingly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile the proposed `.codex/config.toml` (repo root) against the existing `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` prior art: decide whether to retire/redirect the shim, make the shim a symlink to the root file, or update `docs/session-id-shims.md` to reflect the new canonical location — and document that decision in the plan.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml exists as a tracked file with header: 'Copy this fragment into ~/.codex/config.toml (see docs/session-id-shims.md)'","docs/session-id-shims.md:90-91 documents: 'Copy `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` into `~/.codex/config.toml`'","Plan proposes committing a NEW `.codex/config.toml` at the repo root without mentioning the existing shim or how the two files relate"],"finding":"The plan introduces a new `.codex/config.toml` at the repo root without reconciling it against the already-tracked `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`, which `docs/session-id-shims.md` explicitly describes as 'Copy this fragment into `~/.codex/config.toml`' — the same conceptual file for the same purpose. Committing a second Codex config artifact under a different path risks contradictory content and confuses future maintainers about which is authoritative.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fda73f1b748c9a0ca","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Commit the Codex config: bring `.codex/config.toml` under version control'; Scope section: 'In: … `.codex/config.toml`'","norm_id":"nba9810c992c2cd0b","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Both files coexist with diverging content (e.g., the shim still points at CLAUDE.md while the new root file points at AGENTS.md), creating a confusing discrepancy.","Developers following docs/session-id-shims.md copy the shim file and get stale content; developers using the repo-root `.codex/config.toml` natively get updated content — two populations with different behavior."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Cite a source (Antigravity docs URL, version, or spike result) for the claim that `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so the chosen reference-and-summary approach is traceable and the decision is not revisited unnecessarily.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","No citation or verification source for this Antigravity capability claim","Search of repo files finds no 'Antigravity' documentation or prior-art that confirms or denies @-import support"],"finding":"The plan states 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports' as a verified fact, and bases the design choice (write a reference-and-summary instead of using an import/symlink) on this claim — but no citation, doc link, or prior-art check is provided. If the claim is wrong, the plan's chosen approach creates an ongoing maintenance artifact (the `.agents/rules/rebar.md` summary) that could drift from `AGENTS.md` rather than simply referencing it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4c5521a090238d53","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the generic rules file' bullet: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","norm_id":"n0ceeb745ef65ee25","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If Antigravity does support an include/import mechanism, the plan's chosen approach is unnecessarily complex and creates a content-drift risk between the summary and AGENTS.md.","A future contributor finds the Antigravity docs, discovers @-imports exist, and must redo the work or maintain two diverging docs."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a parenthetical in the plan like: '(confirmed: Antigravity rules format v<X> has no include/import directive — see <URL or spike ticket>)'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either (a) add docs/experiments CLAUDE.md references (criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500, make_crit_v7.py:181) to this story's owned-file list and remove ':!docs/experiments' from the AC1 proving command, or (b) explicitly attribute docs/experiments to a named sibling story (or a new follow-up), and update the parent's Out list to document the carve-out.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent epic scope: 'In: the root guidance files, docs/ homes for CLAUDE.md-native content, the .codex/.agents shims, examples/ skills, a client template + drift test, and a repo-wide reference sweep.'","Parent epic Out list: 'Out: changing rebar's runtime behavior, the Gerrit/CI landing flow itself, or Jira sync.' — docs/experiments is not listed as out-of-scope.","Leaf AC1 proving command excludes ':!docs/experiments' with no attribution to another sibling story.","Actual CLAUDE.md references exist in docs/experiments: criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500, make_crit_v7.py:181 (confirmed by search_files).","By contrast, docs/event-schema.md is explicitly attributed to S1, and examples/ is explicitly attributed to S5 — docs/experiments has no such attribution."],"finding":"The leaf silently excludes docs/experiments from its CLAUDE.md reference sweep (via ':!docs/experiments' in the AC1 proving command) without assigning that sub-scope to any sibling story, creating an unowned gap in the parent's declared 'repo-wide reference sweep.'","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd6771c3c9b6de547","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Leaf AC1 proving command; Scope section ('Out: files owned by S1/S5, CHANGELOG.md, the root-file/template changes'); parent epic Scope ('In: … a repo-wide reference sweep')","norm_id":"nf0605a7d61dda1db","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["When all child stories close and 'git grep CLAUDE.md' is run repo-wide (excluding only CHANGELOG.md and CLAUDE.md itself), docs/experiments hits remain, violating the parent's 'repo-wide sweep' success criterion.","A future reviewer or agent reading AGENTS.md and then encountering old criteria JSON in docs/experiments still referencing CLAUDE.md gets inconsistent guidance."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a citation or doc link for the Antigravity `@`-import limitation (e.g., a URL to Antigravity's rules-file documentation), or note it as an assumption-under-uncertainty rather than a stated fact.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","search_files for 'Antigravity' returns zero hits in tracked repo files","Evidence class: Unverified — no doc link, no --help reference, no prior-art check cited in plan"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports' as a known technical fact, using it to justify writing a short reference-and-summary rather than a direct file reference or symlink. The term 'Antigravity' does not appear anywhere in the repo's tracked files or documentation, making this an unverified capability claim about an unidentified external provider. If the assertion is wrong (i.e., `@`-imports are supported), the design choice is suboptimal and the committed `.agents/rules/rebar.md` may duplicate content unnecessarily.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3b8c93d2757996e5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the generic rules file' bullet: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","norm_id":"n9420a454ef9506eb","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If Antigravity does support @-imports, the rules file becomes a prose summary that drifts from AGENTS.md over time instead of a single canonical pointer, creating a maintenance burden.","If the capability claim is wrong, a future contributor updating AGENTS.md must also update .agents/rules/rebar.md manually."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["F1","E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"AC1's proving command cannot pass within a single working session for this story because it explicitly requires S1 and S5 to have already landed ('After this story AND its S1/S5 dependencies land'). A developer completing only this story's 17-file edits will see the command return non-zero (S1/S5 files still contain 'CLAUDE.md'), making the criterion unmeasurable in isolation for this ticket.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6f036c8c1ede2c7e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, first bullet (AC1)","norm_id":"n503bb81642ac11c5","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a new AC (before the existing AC1) that runs `git grep -l 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- <the 17 owned files listed in the plan>` and asserts it returns empty. Relabel the existing AC1 as an integration check that fires only after S1 and S5 have merged, or move it to the epic-level definition-of-done.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Capture the 'provider configs are committed and team-shared' policy decision in a persistent location (an ADR entry, a new AGENTS.md section, or a CONTRIBUTING.md note) so future contributors know to commit new provider config files.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e","T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The Assumption section says 'If the team wants provider configs to stay per-developer/local, drop those two bullets' — this is a live architectural choice, not a settled one","The repo already has docs/adr/ (referenced in scope: docs/adr/0043-…:121 is one of the 17 owned files) — the team clearly uses ADRs for decisions of this kind","No ADR or AGENTS.md section is planned to record the 'provider configs are committed, team-shared' policy","ABSENCE: the plan adds no design-doc update capturing this policy for future contributors deciding whether to add a new provider config file"],"finding":"The decision to bring provider config files (.codex/config.toml, .agents/rules/rebar.md) into version control as a team-shared artifact is a novel policy/architectural decision that affects all contributors and future provider onboarding, but it is not persisted in an ADR or design doc — only in the plan's transient Assumption section.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f44b9e0819ffab1d2","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## Assumption (flag for override) and ## What — 'Commit the Codex config' / 'Commit the generic rules file' bullets","norm_id":"n6d52b0df937e8e62","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A new team member adds a .cursor/rules config locally and doesn't realise it should be committed, because the policy is nowhere documented persistently","A future story adding Gemini config has no written precedent to follow and must rediscover the convention"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a brief note to CONTRIBUTING.md (in the same edit that fixes line 570) or to AGENTS.md explaining that provider-shim config files (.codex/, .agents/rules/) are tracked in version control and should be updated when AGENTS.md changes, and optionally open a follow-up ADR for the per-tool pointer decision.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Expand the CONTRIBUTING.md edit to include a sentence or section noting that .codex/config.toml and .agents/rules/rebar.md are tracked provider-shim configs that should be kept in sync with AGENTS.md.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The plan says CONTRIBUTING.md:570 is updated (CLAUDE.md → AGENTS.md) but specifies no additional content about the two newly tracked provider config files","ABSENCE: no AC or plan bullet says 'CONTRIBUTING.md mentions .codex/config.toml and .agents/rules/rebar.md as tracked provider configs'","The newly tracked files are a new artifact class in the repo; without a doc pointer, contributors have no discoverable path to find them"],"finding":"CONTRIBUTING.md line 570 is updated to replace the CLAUDE.md reference, but the plan does not specify that the update also adds guidance about the newly tracked .codex/config.toml and .agents/rules/rebar.md artifacts — leaving no discoverable doc path for contributors who need to know these files exist.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7dd4415ee998121c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — 'CONTRIBUTING.md:570' in the 17-file list; ## Acceptance Criteria — AC 1","norm_id":"nf1f92f5ae58b8dbd","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A contributor searching CONTRIBUTING.md for 'how do I set up provider X' finds no mention of .codex/ or .agents/rules/ and duplicates config locally, defeating the point of committing them"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the CONTRIBUTING.md hunk that fixes line 570, add a short paragraph under the AI/provider tooling heading: 'Provider config files (.codex/config.toml, .agents/rules/rebar.md) are committed to the repository so all clones and providers share the same guidance. Update them if AGENTS.md changes significantly.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define the update-ownership lifecycle for the newly-committed `.codex/config.toml` and `.agents/rules/rebar.md`: specify who is responsible for keeping them in sync with `AGENTS.md`, whether/how developers may maintain local overrides post-commit, and add a note (e.g. a comment in rebar.md or a CI lint) to flag drift when `AGENTS.md` changes.","cohort":["T12","T5b","T9"],"criteria":["T9"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'.codex/config.toml and .agents/rules/rebar.md are untracked, locally .git/info/exclude'd files on one machine' — plan acknowledges prior per-developer model","'bring .codex/config.toml under version control (git add -f, it is currently locally excluded)' — transitions to shared state with no ownership spec","'a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink' for rebar.md — creates a maintenance coupling to AGENTS.md with no stated sync process","ABSENCE: no mention of who owns future edits, how local-only Codex configs are handled post-commit, or a retirement/replacement path for these files"],"finding":"The plan transitions `.codex/config.toml` and `.agents/rules/rebar.md` from per-developer, locally-excluded files to shared git-tracked state, but does not specify the ongoing update ownership model: who is responsible for keeping these files current, whether developers can still maintain local overrides (and how, given the prior `.git/info/exclude` mechanism is now moot), and what happens when `AGENTS.md` changes and `rebar.md`'s reference-and-summary drifts.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f45b77e43205ca383","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — 'Commit the Codex config' and 'Commit the generic rules file' bullets; ## Scope","norm_id":"n14f29867ecd5ef18","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Developer A needs a local Codex config pointing at a fork; previously used git/info/exclude, now must either commit a conflicting change or maintain an untracked override with no documented approach.","AGENTS.md is updated in story S4/S5; rebar.md's summary silently drifts, causing Antigravity to get stale guidance with no alert or defined sync owner."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a brief 'Maintenance' note to the plan: (1) designate ownership (e.g. 'any PR that modifies AGENTS.md must also update .agents/rules/rebar.md — enforced by a grep in pre-commit or CI'); (2) document the local-override path for Codex (e.g. 'developers needing a local-only config should add a `.codex/config.local.toml` entry to .gitignore after this story lands'); (3) add the sync check to the AC proving step.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a positive rationale to the plan explaining why committing a repo-root `.codex/config.toml` (rather than updating the existing `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` and its documentation) achieves the goal of making guidance available to providers — and address the relationship between the two Codex config files.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Why section: only explains the problem ('untracked, locally excluded') without stating why repo-root committed files are superior to extending the existing `scripts/session-shims/` pattern","Existing `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` is already tracked in version control — the plan does not explain how the new `.codex/config.toml` differs in purpose or runtime effect","Assumption section acknowledges the team may want per-developer configs, but does not weigh the two approaches"],"finding":"The plan provides no positive rationale for committing provider configs to the repo root as the chosen approach, versus extending the existing `scripts/session-shims/` copy-to-home pattern (which already tracks `codex-config.toml` in source control and documents the copy step). The 'Why' section explains only the *problem* (files are untracked), not why repo-root committed configs are the right solution given the existing per-developer shim infrastructure.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9e081b95ca9bca61","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Why section; Assumption section; 'Commit the Codex config' and 'Commit the generic rules file' bullets in What","norm_id":"n9d09052e56fac592","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Implementer asks: 'Why not just update the existing scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml to reference AGENTS.md and update the docs?' — the plan has no answer.","Two tracked Codex config files (scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml and .codex/config.toml) with different content and no stated relationship create confusion for future maintainers."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either remove AC2 as redundant with AC1's sweep, or repurpose it to verify that AGENTS.md is present in those specific files (the replacement half of the migration check).","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["AC1 excludes only: CLAUDE.md, CHANGELOG.md, docs/event-schema.md, examples/, docs/experiments/","AC2 targets: src/rebar/llm and docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md — none of these are in AC1's exclusion list","AC2 proving: '[ \"$(git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- src/rebar/llm docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md ...)\" = 0 ]' is a strict subset of AC1's sweep"],"finding":"AC2 is a near-duplicate of AC1 for a strict subset of files. The files targeted by AC2 (src/rebar/llm/*, docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md) are already swept by AC1's proving command (they are not in AC1's exclusion list), so AC2 adds no independent verification.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2c084c3cbd82437b","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC2","norm_id":"n0347aa54f66a59a0","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Redundant CI steps run the same check twice, giving a false sense of additional coverage without adding new verification value."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.8333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm that Antigravity is a current, active provider deployment target (cite a confirmed use-case or epic AC), and add at least one doc reference or link for the `@`-import limitation claim; if Antigravity is not in-scope for the current epic's done-definition, defer `.agents/rules/rebar.md` to a follow-up story.","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Search for 'Antigravity' across the repo returns zero tracked-file hits (only cached plan-review findings reference it)","Search for 'agents/rules' returns zero tracked-file hits","No existing `.agents/` directory appears in the repo root listing","The plan's own parenthetical justifies the format choice with an unverified capability claim: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports' — no doc link or prior-art cited"],"finding":"The plan introduces `.agents/rules/rebar.md` as a new config surface for 'Antigravity', a provider with zero existing presence in the tracked codebase or documentation. This is a single-consumer, unverified-need config artifact — failing the Rule-of-Three and YAGNI tests for new config surfaces.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f26709a26748e177e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the generic rules file' bullet; Scope section — 'In: … .agents/rules/rebar.md'","norm_id":"nfa5f7f6ec638d2e3","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If Antigravity is never deployed against this repo, the .agents/rules/rebar.md file is dead weight with no consumers.","If the capability assertion about @-imports is wrong (the plan provides no citation), implementors may create an unnecessarily verbose file when a shorter include would work."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"sever